data.enText: hesitating before doing sth because you do not want to do it or because you are not sure that it is the right thing to do
She was reluctant to admit she was wrong.

data.chText: 他最后露出了一丝无可奈何的微笑。
data.enText: He finally gave a reluctant smile.
a reluctant hero (= a person who does not want to be called a hero)

data.chText: 雇主们仍然不太愿意参加这项工程。
data.enText: There is still some reluctance on the part of employers to become involved in this project.

data.chText: 他们最终有点勉强地同意了我们的条件。
data.enText: They finally agreed to our terms with a certain reluctance.

data.chText: 我们勉强答应跟她一起去。
data.enText: We reluctantly agreed to go with her.

ex.chText: 他不愿意提及过去的经历。
ex.enText: He was reluctant to mention his past experiences.

ex.chText: 他的女友只是勉强笑了笑。
ex.enText: His girlfriend just gave a reluctant smile.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事很不情愿或很犹豫的。

ex.chText: 为什么他不愿告诉朋友他的公司遇到困难了？
ex.enText: Why was he loath to tell his friend that his company was in trouble?

ex.chText: 青春期的学生通常不愿意和父母聊学校的事。
ex.enText: Adolescent students are usually loath to chat with their parents about what happened in school.

synonyms.bx: 指不愿意做某事的，通常用于 be loath to do sth 结构中。

ex.chText: 她要么是不愿意借，要么就是根本没有那本书。
ex.enText: She was either unwilling or she just didn't have that book.

ex.chText: 经理没有办法，只好付钱给那些不情愿的帮忙者。
ex.enText: The manager had no choice but to pay those unwilling helpers.

synonyms.bx: 作“不愿意的”解时，表示不想做某事而且予以拒绝，只作表语；作“不情愿的”解时，表示不想做某事但还是做了，只作定语。

example: foreigners stubbornly reluctant to accept our ways
fresh from college and reluctant for the moment to marry him
they were usually reluctant to socialize

tr: unwillingness to do something contrary to your custom

value.def: If you are reluctant to do something, you are unwilling to do it and hesitate before doing it, or do it slowly and without enthusiasm.

example.ex: Mr Spero was reluctant to ask for help...
example.tran: 斯佩罗先生不愿意寻求帮助。

example.ex: The police are very reluctant to get involved in this sort of thing.
example.tran: 警方很不愿意卷入这类事情。

example.ex: We have reluctantly agreed to let him go.
example.tran: 我们不情愿地同意放他走。

example.ex: Ministers have shown extreme reluctance to explain their position to the media.
example.tran: 部长们极不情愿向媒体解释他们的立场。

trans: 不愿意；不甘心情愿做；不愿；勉强的；不情愿的
